    {
      "type": "html",
      "text": " The four scales (Introvert vs Extrovert, iNtuition vs Sensation, Thinking vs Feeling, Perceiving vs Judging) vary independently. This means that Myers-Briggs sorts the world into sixteen boxes, a set large enough to encompass wide human variation. (People are not evenly distributed over these types; some combinations are quite rare.)  <i>How does having four binary scales and sixteen possible results ensure the accuracy of the results?  Quantity does not equal quality.</i>",
      "id": "bc5b7e437a6cff20bdf5e9c0597eba12"
